title: S. Jersey Boys: Hermits' Tabora ties mark in win
text:
Devin Plumlee scored two goals for Maple Shade in a 3-2 victory over host Pemberton in Burlington County League play. 
Plumlee also had an assist on a goal scored by Doran Keys. 
In other Burlington County League action: 
Mat Shaddow netted two goals in a 3-1 victory for Holy Cross against host New Egypt. It was Coach Tom Guida's 100th win. 
Mike Deal made 19 saves for Rancocas Valley, The Inquirer's top-ranked team in South Jersey, in a 1-1 draw against visiting Cinnaminson. Alex Begolly scored for Rancocas Valley and Sean Bockius scored for Cinnaminson. 
Brad Forman scored a hat trick for host Northern Burlington in a 3-0 win over third-ranked Burlington Township. Logan Amey made five saves. 
Timothy McHale scored two goals on the field and made six saves in net for Medford Tech in a 6-0 win at Willingboro. Jacob Powell also made six saves and scored a goal. 
Harry Inglis scored a hat trick for Moorestown in a 7-3 win against host Pennsauken. Ross Lazarus also scored. 
Tri-County Diamond. Bryan Sanchez notched a hat trick for Penns Grove in a 5-4 overtime victory at Deptford. Austin Lehr and Jacuquan McPherson also scored. 
Tri-County Royal. Justin Curtin netted three goals in No. 4 Williamstown's 4-0 win at GCIT. Kenny Ezeiruaku also scored. 
Vincent Petulla notched a goal and an assist in host Hammonton's 3-0 win against Kingsway. Vincent Mocarski and Vincent Piccari also scored. 
Tri-County Classic. Josh Schmidt tallied two goals and an assist in Pennsville's 6-1 win against visiting Gloucester. Ryan Cruice, Max Dineen, Josh White, and C.J. Widger also scored. 
Nonleague. Isaiah Rodriguez and Mert Tokac each scored for host Westampton Tech in a 2-1 victory against Baptist Regional. 
Brothers Brenden and Jeremy Rafanello each scored for Delran in a 2-0 win at Clearview. Skylar Diggs had an assist. 
Nick Grotti scored a hat trick for Millville as it cruised past host Woodstown, 5-0. Ryan McIsaac and Andrew Sooy also scored.
